1
00:00:08,538 --> 00:00:08,958
Sorry.

2
00:00:08,978 --> 00:00:11,419
I'm told visiting
hours are over.

3
00:00:14,260 --> 00:00:16,341
I'm an executioner named Draht.

4
00:00:16,761 --> 00:00:18,221
I serve Aura, the guillotine.

5
00:00:18,461 --> 00:00:19,122
Don't fight.

6
00:00:19,942 --> 00:00:21,382
I have come here to kill you.

7
00:00:22,843 --> 00:00:23,343
I see.

8
00:00:24,063 --> 00:00:25,784
Not pretending you
want peace anymore?

9
00:00:26,904 --> 00:00:27,685
We've just begun.

10
00:00:27,705 --> 00:00:34,567
I should warn you
that I am fairly strong.

11
00:00:36,408 --> 00:00:37,028
Stronger than me?

12
00:00:38,815 --> 00:00:40,957
Stronger even than
Aura the guillotine.

13
00:00:43,859 --> 00:00:45,260
I doubt that very much.

14
00:00:46,021 --> 00:00:46,281
Why?

15
00:00:49,743 --> 00:00:50,084
Why?

16
00:00:50,364 --> 00:00:52,025
For this fight is already over.

17
00:00:56,529 --> 00:00:57,830
A magical wire, huh?

18
00:00:58,490 --> 00:00:59,791
What an interesting spell.

19
00:01:00,592 --> 00:01:04,014
You concentrated mana around
your neck to avoid decapitation.

20
00:01:04,855 --> 00:01:05,776
You're level-headed.

21
00:01:06,792 --> 00:01:10,215
which allowed you to keep your head when
an ordinary mage would have lost theirs.

22
00:01:11,616 --> 00:01:15,260
Try what you will, but this wire is
among demonkind's strongest spells.

23
00:01:16,080 --> 00:01:19,944
Humanity's feeble magic
doesn't stand a chance!

24
00:01:21,205 --> 00:01:24,568
I shall saw through your mana
and the soft pink flesh underneath.

25
00:01:25,749 --> 00:01:26,329
You're right.

26
00:01:27,010 --> 00:01:29,592
I doubt there is anything I
can do to sever your thread.

27
00:01:31,725 --> 00:01:32,125
Really?

28
00:01:32,325 --> 00:01:34,267
That's all it took to
convince you you'd won?

29
00:01:34,727 --> 00:01:36,529
Demons these days
are such a disgrace.

30
00:01:36,849 --> 00:01:38,510
No experience
on the battlefield.

31
00:01:44,955 --> 00:01:47,596
This mage... She took my arm!

32
00:01:48,437 --> 00:01:53,601
You big child!

33
00:01:56,043 --> 00:01:57,083
Let's talk this through!

34
00:02:07,531 --> 00:02:08,772
That's one beast down.

35
00:02:13,117 --> 00:02:19,683
If I report this attack to the Graf and exterminate the rest of
the town's parasites, a pardon is the least he could grant me.

36
00:02:29,833 --> 00:02:31,615
This is going to
complicate things.

37
00:04:10,618 --> 00:04:11,939
This food is delicious.

38
00:04:15,424 --> 00:04:19,911
My master always said, you can tell if a
town is peaceful by how good the eats are.

39
00:04:21,413 --> 00:04:22,895
Guess that goes
for this place too.

40
00:04:30,175 --> 00:04:30,955
Mr. Stark.

41
00:04:31,376 --> 00:04:32,416
No, order your own.

42
00:04:33,797 --> 00:04:34,897
Let's talk to the Graf.

43
00:04:35,037 --> 00:04:38,038
We can try to petition him
directly to release Mistress Frieren.

44
00:04:41,040 --> 00:04:43,881
It's only a matter of time
until harm comes to this town.

45
00:04:45,402 --> 00:04:48,543
If we can get her out of the
dungeon, she can defeat the demons.

46
00:04:52,312 --> 00:04:54,032
That does feel
like our only option.

47
00:04:54,733 --> 00:04:56,873
We don't stand a chance
against enemies like those.

48
00:04:58,133 --> 00:04:59,794
Especially not the Lügner guy.

49
00:05:00,274 --> 00:05:01,354
He seems dangerous.

50
00:05:02,935 --> 00:05:04,455
He only looked at Frieren.

51
00:05:05,635 --> 00:05:08,276
We were standing right there
next to him with the guards.

52
00:05:09,796 --> 00:05:11,757
But his eyes were
locked on her alone.

53
00:05:15,037 --> 00:05:17,638
He saw us as pawns that
he can knock out anytime.

54
00:05:19,298 --> 00:05:21,179
My hands haven't
stopped shaking since.

55
00:05:27,550 --> 00:05:27,950
You see?

56
00:05:28,511 --> 00:05:30,451
One thought about him
and I'm spilling my drink.

57
00:05:31,451 --> 00:05:32,952
Now it looks like I wet myself.

58
00:05:34,232 --> 00:05:35,553
We have an important meeting.

59
00:05:36,213 --> 00:05:36,793
Clean it up.

60
00:05:39,074 --> 00:05:41,034
Graf Granat is with
Lügner and his men.

61
00:05:42,855 --> 00:05:44,135
Maybe asking for a fight.

62
00:05:45,015 --> 00:05:47,456
What wouldn't have stopped
the heroes should not stop us.

63
00:05:52,598 --> 00:05:53,118
You're right.

64
00:05:54,257 --> 00:05:57,958
If I lost my nerve here, I'd never
be able to face my master again.

65
00:05:59,358 --> 00:05:59,838
Let's go!

66
00:06:01,619 --> 00:06:02,799
You can hang on to that one.

67
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:10,261
Are you coming?

68
00:06:11,481 --> 00:06:12,921
My body seems to think not.

69
00:06:18,422 --> 00:06:20,583
I am no longer
detecting Draht's mana.

70
00:06:23,868 --> 00:06:24,729
He must be dead.

71
00:06:25,750 --> 00:06:26,510
What a fool.

72
00:06:27,391 --> 00:06:28,332
He was careless.

73
00:06:30,213 --> 00:06:30,814
Careless?

74
00:06:32,715 --> 00:06:36,719
We are the right-hand men
of Lady Aura, her executioners.

75
00:06:38,260 --> 00:06:40,281
You think mere
carelessness could kill us?

76
00:06:42,864 --> 00:06:44,865
Just who exactly is that mage?

77
00:06:51,511 --> 00:06:53,172
Apologies for
keeping you waiting.

78
00:06:55,790 --> 00:07:00,712
It seems the mage I captured managed to
escape, and her guard was found beheaded.

79
00:07:01,633 --> 00:07:03,094
A worrisome threat to peace.

80
00:07:03,594 --> 00:07:05,035
We shall help you
with your search.

81
00:07:05,735 --> 00:07:08,796
Linie is quite skilled at
detecting mine- No, we're fine.

82
00:07:12,198 --> 00:07:12,758
Peculiar.

83
00:07:13,579 --> 00:07:16,060
It appears that you are
missing one of your companions.

84
00:07:17,080 --> 00:07:17,921
He'll be back soon.

85
00:07:18,541 --> 00:07:19,582
He went to use the privy.

86
00:07:20,262 --> 00:07:22,243
Without asking a
servant where it is.

87
00:07:25,527 --> 00:07:28,609
My untrained eye can tell
that mage is of great skill.

88
00:07:30,510 --> 00:07:33,111
Yet she allowed my men
to detain her without a fight.

89
00:07:34,812 --> 00:07:37,293
She understands the
gravity of killing a guard.

90
00:07:39,615 --> 00:07:42,636
Lord Lügner, I'll ask
you one last time.

91
00:07:47,699 --> 00:07:49,400
Where is your other companion?

92
00:08:08,132 --> 00:08:09,674
That idiot, Draht.

93
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:20,881
He has ruined everything.

94
00:08:36,934 --> 00:08:38,595
Yet I find I can't complain.

95
00:08:40,075 --> 00:08:43,656
For now it seems that violence is the
only way to resolve this predicament.

96
00:08:44,637 --> 00:08:49,658
It would be a lie to say I'm
anything less than overjoyed.

97
00:08:49,698 --> 00:08:55,880
Whatever you use to reason, be it words or swords,
the end result will ultimately be the same.

98
00:08:57,461 --> 00:09:00,582
No matter your weapon
of choice, the weak will die.

99
00:09:03,638 --> 00:09:05,878
Just like this sword's
former owner did.

100
00:09:07,279 --> 00:09:16,221
Lügner!

101
00:09:18,741 --> 00:09:19,181
You see?

102
00:09:19,841 --> 00:09:21,222
We are but wild beasts.

103
00:09:22,702 --> 00:09:23,462
But don't worry.

104
00:09:24,122 --> 00:09:25,143
I won't kill you.

105
00:09:28,103 --> 00:09:31,404
You're going to assist us in
removing this town's defensive barrier.

106
00:09:37,655 --> 00:09:39,216
Shouldn't be too
much farther from here.

107
00:09:44,241 --> 00:09:44,922
Excuse me.

108
00:09:49,100 --> 00:09:50,225
That is you, isn't it?

109
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:01,109
Aren't you supposed
to be in jail?

110
00:10:01,637 --> 00:10:03,419
Please don't tell me
that you broke out.

111
00:10:05,033 --> 00:10:06,514
I didn't have a
choice in the matter.

112
00:10:07,695 --> 00:10:10,897
A demon called Draht came
into my cell trying to execute me.

113
00:10:11,717 --> 00:10:17,281
And though I took care of the issue, when demons
die they turn into monoparticles and vanish.

114
00:10:18,922 --> 00:10:20,343
I don't understand
the connection.

115
00:10:21,283 --> 00:10:24,205
Before visiting me, he killed
the man guarding the dungeon.

116
00:10:25,026 --> 00:10:30,229
To better paint the scene, all to be found down
there was a guard beheaded by a magical wire.

117
00:10:30,929 --> 00:10:31,870
And a lone mage.

118
00:10:33,703 --> 00:10:34,984
So where might that put me?

119
00:10:35,004 --> 00:10:39,246
You'll be sentenced to
death for killing the guard.

120
00:10:39,646 --> 00:10:40,466
I think so too.

121
00:10:41,187 --> 00:10:43,388
Which is why I have no
choice but to leave town.

122
00:10:44,028 --> 00:10:44,708
Wait a moment.

123
00:10:45,529 --> 00:10:48,130
If you leave, the remaining
demons will run wild.

124
00:10:48,990 --> 00:10:50,671
Would you really
abandon these people?

125
00:10:52,872 --> 00:10:54,533
Why don't you two
defeat them for me?

126
00:10:55,293 --> 00:10:57,254
You make it sound
like an everyday chore.

127
00:10:57,955 --> 00:11:00,556
We don't stand a chance in a
fight against monsters like them.

128
00:11:01,447 --> 00:11:03,829
You're not going to fight them
just because they're strong?

129
00:11:07,393 --> 00:11:08,714
Don't look so downcast.

130
00:11:08,994 --> 00:11:17,122
I've fought more than my fair share of
demons, and you're no weaker than they are.

131
00:11:17,182 --> 00:11:18,263
Okay, we'll fight them!

132
00:11:18,563 --> 00:11:19,664
But you've gotta help us!

133
00:11:20,164 --> 00:11:21,646
You can't ask us to go it alone!

134
00:11:22,006 --> 00:11:22,887
We're begging you!

135
00:11:27,895 --> 00:11:29,857
Hey, where do you
think you're going?

136
00:11:30,017 --> 00:11:31,799
You can't leave
us to die, Frieren.

137
00:11:31,819 --> 00:11:33,160
You don't know when to give up.

138
00:11:33,601 --> 00:11:35,042
Steel your resolve, remember?

139
00:11:35,703 --> 00:11:36,704
Steel yourself.

140
00:11:37,520 --> 00:11:39,320
I don't wanna be demon food.

141
00:11:39,520 --> 00:11:40,920
You're being childish.

142
00:11:50,923 --> 00:11:55,865
About ten kilometers outside of
town, I sense a great deal of mana.

143
00:11:57,006 --> 00:11:58,407
Someone is observing us.

144
00:12:16,615 --> 00:12:20,137
Aura the Guillotine, one of the
Seven Sages of Destruction.

145
00:12:22,341 --> 00:12:25,285
It isn't as if I enjoy facing
powerful enemies either.

146
00:12:29,271 --> 00:12:31,715
All the more reason to
take care of this one swiftly.

147
00:13:23,720 --> 00:13:24,641
This feels wrong.

148
00:13:25,261 --> 00:13:26,662
You're sure we have to sneak in?

149
00:13:28,043 --> 00:13:32,511
Well, I suppose we could just tell the gate
guards we're here to kill the peace envoys.

150
00:13:49,480 --> 00:13:51,042
It's a little too quiet.

151
00:14:00,393 --> 00:14:02,975
I truly love magic, you see.

152
00:14:05,036 --> 00:14:07,298
Think of Qual, the
Elder Sage of Corruption.

153
00:14:08,359 --> 00:14:10,300
His life revolved around magic.

154
00:14:11,141 --> 00:14:14,303
That was the price for
developing his killing spell.

155
00:14:17,825 --> 00:14:19,206
Such is the way of our kind.

156
00:14:19,386 --> 00:14:24,530
We devote ourselves to research and spend our
lengthy lives studying a single type of magic.

157
00:14:25,762 --> 00:14:28,743
We grow our knowledge
daily for years upon years.

158
00:14:29,923 --> 00:14:37,325
Our magics might impress you now, but wait a decade and our
powers will be even greater, further cementing our strength.

159
00:14:41,426 --> 00:14:45,207
Yet, magic is a strange thing.

160
00:14:46,868 --> 00:14:54,730
This town's defensive barrier, created by Flamme the
Legendary Mage, has successfully kept demons out.

161
00:15:18,421 --> 00:15:25,704
A spell cast by a genius a thousand years ago can
sometimes outmatch the research of the present.

162
00:15:29,166 --> 00:15:30,626
I despise geniuses.

163
00:15:31,667 --> 00:15:34,188
The beauty of accumulated
effort is lost on them.

164
00:15:36,569 --> 00:15:39,090
Your family knows about
this barrier better than any.

165
00:15:39,390 --> 00:15:41,091
You've maintained
it for generations.

166
00:15:42,391 --> 00:15:45,873
You showed your hand when you
allowed our demonic presence into town.

167
00:15:46,590 --> 00:15:49,311
Now I know Flamme's
creation can be controlled.

168
00:15:50,912 --> 00:15:52,153
You will teach me how.

169
00:15:58,076 --> 00:15:59,897
Perhaps you need
a moment to think.

170
00:16:02,778 --> 00:16:03,939
I will leave you for now.

171
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:09,902
Making someone wait is a diplomatic
tactic we demons can employ as well.

172
00:16:11,863 --> 00:16:15,585
If you refuse to speak with me,
know that further torture awaits.

173
00:16:25,476 --> 00:16:28,479
There must be a grimoire related
to the barrier hidden somewhere.

174
00:16:29,400 --> 00:16:30,141
Search his room.

175
00:16:30,701 --> 00:16:31,923
I shall search the study.

176
00:16:46,303 --> 00:16:46,843
It's you.

177
00:16:47,384 --> 00:16:49,165
That snot-nosed adventurer kid.

178
00:16:49,845 --> 00:16:52,226
I thought my son had
come to take me away.

179
00:16:52,927 --> 00:16:53,827
You look awful.

180
00:16:54,628 --> 00:16:55,989
Those demons are no joke.

181
00:16:58,010 --> 00:16:58,790
Let me help you out.

182
00:17:05,654 --> 00:17:06,795
Your hands are trembling.

183
00:17:07,115 --> 00:17:07,955
Is that a problem?

184
00:17:08,656 --> 00:17:08,916
No.

185
00:17:09,476 --> 00:17:10,137
It is valiant.

186
00:17:11,717 --> 00:17:14,359
My son's hands trembled
before he marched into battle, too.

187
00:17:21,327 --> 00:17:22,729
Must've cast a
spell on the rope.

188
00:17:23,189 --> 00:17:23,950
It won't cut.

189
00:17:24,931 --> 00:17:25,891
Just leave me be.

190
00:17:26,952 --> 00:17:28,073
I'm already done for.

191
00:17:29,455 --> 00:17:31,637
Evacuate the townsfolk
while you still can.

192
00:17:32,297 --> 00:17:36,121
You don't know your people if you think
they'd listen to a snot-nosed adventure kid.

193
00:17:36,841 --> 00:17:39,364
The Granat family crest
hangs from my neck.

194
00:17:42,266 --> 00:17:44,929
Show it to the guards and
they'll do whatever you say.

195
00:17:47,252 --> 00:17:48,512
And watch your tone with me.

196
00:17:49,513 --> 00:17:52,574
The way that you've spoken
thus far is a serious offense.

197
00:18:00,177 --> 00:18:02,617
Although, I could
overlook your crime.

198
00:18:03,938 --> 00:18:04,738
If you run now.

199
00:18:05,719 --> 00:18:06,199
I get it.

200
00:18:07,579 --> 00:18:08,520
Sorry, old-timer.

201
00:18:10,600 --> 00:18:12,461
You better kiss your
fancy chair goodbye.

202
00:18:15,113 --> 00:18:17,075
No chance I can
afford to replace him!

203
00:18:18,576 --> 00:18:20,398
Lord Lugnia, it's a rat.

204
00:18:23,902 --> 00:18:26,004
Graf Granat, do you know him?

205
00:18:26,725 --> 00:18:27,125
I don't.

206
00:18:27,665 --> 00:18:29,427
He's one of the
travelers passing through.

207
00:18:31,029 --> 00:18:35,093
He must have come to ask me to free that
mage without realizing she's already escaped.

208
00:18:36,957 --> 00:18:38,298
He's just a stupid boy.

209
00:18:39,858 --> 00:18:40,318
I see.

210
00:18:41,999 --> 00:18:42,519
Again...

211
00:18:43,700 --> 00:18:44,780
You can be on your way.

212
00:18:45,860 --> 00:18:46,881
I will let you live.

213
00:18:47,581 --> 00:18:48,522
It's like before.

214
00:18:50,622 --> 00:18:52,063
He's not even looking at me.

215
00:18:54,544 --> 00:18:56,445
Step aside while you still can.

216
00:18:57,325 --> 00:18:58,745
Get in my way and I'll kill you.

217
00:19:03,447 --> 00:19:04,568
I'd like to see you try.

218
00:19:08,917 --> 00:19:12,438
My... Fast.

219
00:19:12,718 --> 00:19:23,940
For a human, that is.

220
00:19:25,760 --> 00:19:28,921
You protected your vitals,
and your reflexes aren't bad.

221
00:19:29,361 --> 00:19:32,942
That said, the young are rash,
whether they're human or demon.

222
00:19:33,542 --> 00:19:35,342
Reckless with no strategy.

223
00:19:37,848 --> 00:19:41,569
Though I have to admit, I do commend
your valor for challenging me on your own.

224
00:19:42,670 --> 00:19:43,330
On my own?

225
00:19:44,210 --> 00:19:44,710
Perfect.

226
00:19:45,050 --> 00:19:48,051
If you can't feel her, I guess
her strategy was a good one.

227
00:19:48,391 --> 00:19:48,911
Come again?

228
00:19:49,652 --> 00:19:52,793
Well, Fern, I created the
opening like you told me to.

229
00:19:54,153 --> 00:19:54,853
Lord Lügner!

230
00:19:54,973 --> 00:19:55,914
I'm sensing a mage.

231
00:20:11,427 --> 00:20:12,188
Impossible.

232
00:20:13,148 --> 00:20:14,909
That mage is a mere human.

233
00:20:15,929 --> 00:20:18,391
She was able to evade
Linie's mana detection.

234
00:20:19,531 --> 00:20:21,913
And beyond that, this spell...

235
00:20:25,594 --> 00:20:26,615
Sit back, my lord.

236
00:20:26,995 --> 00:20:27,856
Let me handle this.

237
00:20:27,956 --> 00:20:28,296
Don't.

238
00:20:29,917 --> 00:20:30,657
Tell me, girl.

239
00:20:31,337 --> 00:20:32,358
What is that spell?

240
00:20:33,623 --> 00:20:35,024
Truly, it's nothing special.

241
00:20:35,964 --> 00:20:37,925
It's just ordinary
offensive magic.

242
00:20:38,485 --> 00:20:40,386
Solltrag in your magic system.

243
00:20:40,486 --> 00:20:42,866
You expect me to
believe that was Solltrag?

244
00:20:43,687 --> 00:20:45,087
Don't be absurd, child.

245
00:20:45,387 --> 00:20:49,969
Demonkind overcame that spell half a century
ago, long before you walked this world.

246
00:20:51,450 --> 00:20:53,250
From whom did
you learn this magic?

247
00:20:54,991 --> 00:20:56,572
You're trying to
buy yourself time.

248
00:20:57,572 --> 00:20:58,332
I'll end this.

249
00:20:59,693 --> 00:21:00,413
You will not.

250
00:21:03,421 --> 00:21:06,343
Fern, his injuries are bad.

251
00:21:07,344 --> 00:21:08,325
There's no time for them.

252
00:21:08,765 --> 00:21:09,366
Let's retreat.

253
00:21:10,907 --> 00:21:11,347
Fine.

254
00:21:22,096 --> 00:21:26,079
Once I stop the bleeding they're
through, I ask you take the warrior.

255
00:21:29,242 --> 00:21:31,564
Those children have
been stained with my blood.

256
00:21:32,790 --> 00:21:33,931
We will not lose them.

257
00:21:35,212 --> 00:21:37,313
You needn't fight her
yourself, Lord Lügner.

258
00:21:38,734 --> 00:21:40,074
I can kill the mage as well.

259
00:21:40,775 --> 00:21:43,857
If it were you who'd been struck
by that spell, you'd be dead.

260
00:21:46,818 --> 00:21:51,901
Already, Mighty, it's been modified from its
base form to specialize in killing demons.

261
00:21:52,902 --> 00:21:56,784
In its current state, it's no
longer Solltrag, Killer of Man.

262
00:21:59,126 --> 00:22:01,047
It has become a
demon-killing spell.

263
00:22:02,483 --> 00:22:06,004
The way that girl moved reminded
me of a mage I faced before.

264
00:22:07,064 --> 00:22:09,845
The same mage who first
struck me with that magic.

265
00:22:21,300 --> 00:22:25,121
Of course, I remember now.

266
00:22:27,067 --> 00:22:28,487
It was Frieren.

267
00:22:30,475 --> 00:22:39,698
The mage who made great contributions to humanity's analysis of
Solltrag and sent more demons to the grave than anyone else in history.

268
00:22:42,820 --> 00:22:44,520
Frieren the Slayer.

269
00:22:46,881 --> 00:22:49,402
One of the geniuses I despise.

